Five celebrities have been unveiled as Tiger Beer Brand Ambassadors even as it launches the #LiveUncaged campaign. The new faces of the brand include BBNaija’s Season Six 1st Runner-up, Liquorose; fast-rising afrobeat singer Ruger; award-winning alternative duo, The Cavemen; and fashion icon, Noble Igwe. At a private event held in Ikoyi, Lagos, recently, celebrities, journalists and friends of the brand gathered to witness the unveiling of the brand ambassadors for the #LiveUncaged experience as brand launches into the Year of The Tiger. Senior brand manager, Tiger Beer, Nigerian Breweries Plc., Beatrice Adeniran expressed her excitement at the occasion, noting, “We are delighted to reveal these five bold mavericks who, against the obstacles in our society, have charted their own course and found their unique voices. Their journey depicts what living uncaged truly means and this event is to celebrate them and recognize them for their courage and unrelenting drive.” The #LiveUncaged campaign promises an exciting ride for lovers of both the beer and the celebrities revealed. The year-long campaign will include media tours to cities across the country, Tiger beer pop up booths and surprise visits to premium locations. There is also the ROAR Live Experience, the Tiger Draught launch and a lot of other fun activities to be unveiled as the year unfolds. With the #LiveUncaged campaign, Tiger Beer urges young Nigerians not to be held down by societal norms and traditions; to reach within unleash their individuality and demonstrate fearlessness in the face of the odds stacked against. 